Element Methods for Updating and Creating DOM Tree

1. appendChild()
2. insertBefore()
3. replaceChild()
4. removeChild()
5. setAttribute()
6. removeAttribute()
7. innerHTML (as a setter)
8. outerHTML (as a setter)
9. textContent (as a setter)
10.className (as a setter)

These methods and properties are specifically used to create or update parts of the DOM tree.